xs is a list of recent x positions, ys is recent y positions.

statistics.pstdev() computes population standard deviation (how spread out the values are).

So pos_std ≈ how jittery the face position has been (in pixels), averaged across x and y:

low pos_std = stable tracking

high pos_std = noisy / shaking / detection jumping

The 999.0 is a “sentinel” default meaning “don’t trust it yet”.

The len >= 6 gate means: don’t compute std dev until you’ve got enough samples.

