That sleep(0.25) is a simple “press lockout” so holding the button doesn’t cycle modes repeatedly.

Cleaner option (recommended): edge-triggered press (no polling)
Instead of checking is_pressed each frame, you can do this once:

Add this in main() after defining handle_c_press():
mode_button.when_pressed = handle_c_press
Then remove all key reading / polling entirely, and your loop just runs normally. Every button press triggers handle_c_press() once.

This is usually the best behavior.

